										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Here are selections from list from a blog of a Protestant theology instructor. I like lists of good books.  I do not know if all the links carried over to this page.<br />
<a href="http://faith-theology.blogspot.com/2009/12/best-books-of-2009.html" target="_blank">Best theology books of 2009</a> from <a href="http://www.google.com/reader/view/feed/http%3A%2F%2Ffaith-theology.blogspot.com%2Ffeeds%2Fposts%2Fdefault" target="_blank">Faith and Theology</a> by Ben Myers</p>
<ul>
<li>Theology: David Kelsey, <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0664220525?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=faithandtheol-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=0664220525" target="_blank">Eccentric Existence: A Theological Anthropology</a>, 2 vols. (WJK)</li>
<li>Biblical studies (OT): John Goldingay, <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0830825630?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=faithandtheol-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=0830825630" target="_blank">Old Testament Theology: Israel&#8217;s Life</a> (IVP)</li>
<li>Systematic theology: T. F. Torrance, <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0830828915?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=faithandtheol-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=0830828915" target="_blank">Incarnation</a> and <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0830828923?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=faithandtheol-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=0830828923" target="_blank">Atonement</a> (IVP)</li>
<li>Essay collection (single author): John Milbank, <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1606081624?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=faithandtheol-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=1606081624" target="_blank">The Future of Love: Essays in Political Theology</a> (Cascade)</li>
<li>Essay collection (multi-author): Oliver Crisp and Michael Rea (eds), <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0199203563?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=faithandtheol-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=0199203563" target="_blank">Analytic Theology: New Essays in the Philosophy of Theology</a> (Oxford UP)</li>
<li>Theological history: John Witte Jr., <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0521548241?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=faithandtheol-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=0521548241" target="_blank">The Sins of the Fathers: The Law and Theology of Illegitimacy Reconsidered</a> (Cambridge UP)</li>
<li>Essay: Sarah Coakley, <a href="http://divinity.uchicago.edu/martycenter/publications/criterion/spring_09.pdf" target="_blank">&#8220;Is There a Future for Gender and Theology? On Gender, Contemplation, and the Systematic Task,&#8221;</a> Criterion 47:1 (2009)</li>
</ul>
<p>Anyone have any recommendations in Jewish thought?</p>
